      "content": "Internal Memo\n\nRe: Enhanced GDPR Compliance Protocols for Client Onboarding Process\n\nIn light of our recent review regarding the GDPR compliance scores, we've refined our process to incorporate a more comprehensive evaluation of key regulatory provisions. \n\nOur revised protocol for client onboarding emphasizes the importance of validation, whereupon our contracts of service must explicitly define roles as both Data Controllers and Data Processors, articulating how \"Right to Erasure\" and \"Data Minimization\" will be respected throughout our engagement. Moreover, our agreements now stipulate the necessity of explicit Consent before collecting sensitive data, specifying the Lawful Basis for our processing activities and referencing the associated Subject Access Request obligations.\n\nWe've also underscored the need for full transparency regarding our data processing methods, including notifications for compliant Breach Response and occurrence of Storage Limitations. Our updated terms explicitly address the Accountability Principle, furnishing explicit obligations on Automated Decision-making and Painstaking Data Protection Impact Assessments, outlined within dedicated arrangements amending Storage Limitations.\n\n  \nguarded integration endeavours clarify what we determine legitimate interests but also preserving current ties to physical data and more, is outlined in protected agreements with integrated processing this separately maintaining \"Special Categories of Data\"(:",
